\subsubsection{Programming the Project}

As noted above, were used and lwjgl Joal libraries to the project schedule.\\

Basically, for the reproduction of the sounds we used the functions provided by OpenAL, which let you load into the space, different sound sources, which in this case were the 2 that are used at random.\\

Subsequently, the user is located within the space, and then you can play the sound giving properties of location, direction and speed, thus, random values were used to reproduce sounds at different locations.\\

In addition, the reproduction of sound in a loop, and also randomizing their location and direction values allowed emulate the feel of battle, added to which was added a 3rd source of background noise.\\

\newpage
\section{Future}

The developed application can serve as an example to initiate development in the world of 3D sound, considering that there are few basic tutorials and examples. In addition, the battle emulated environment, while simple and was easy to program, might well provide a setting for a small game.\\

Regarding the latter, is quite relevant to point out that with little development time achieved a relatively functional programming, and the learning curve, once you have achieved a suitable environment for programming, is not very large, therefore, more investigation the issue is very likely that large applications can be made.\\

Today, most of these applications are for game development, however, the 3D cinema and 3D television is beginning to develop more in that area, or even music videos with 3d sound in fact can be easily found Internet.\\

\newpage
\section{Closure}

While there are many applications, especially games that use 3D sound, there are very few tutorials or guides or examples of easy access to facilitate the development, also, the libraries are not easy to set up or operating system dependent.\\

However, it is noteworthy that the program itself is fairly simple, and has a very small learning curve, so the development of applications using this feature ought not be difficult after overcoming the drawbacks mentioned.\\

It is striking that throughout the investigation and development of the project, all the examples found were experimental or video games, or in rare cases, designed for musical pieces, and were generally small examples, not great based 3d sound applications, but used it as another feature. This is noted because it draws attention not been met, for example, with applications designed for blind or hearing impaired people, etc.\\

Therefore, seems important, for example, the future we may have the cinema and 3D television using this feature, as it could allow a better perception of what happens to people who are visually impaired.\\

